Media Downloader – Chrome Extension
Last Updated: March 3, 2026

1. Overview

Media Downloader is a Chrome extension that allows users to detect and download media files (images, videos, audio files, and SVGs) from the currently active webpage.

We are committed to protecting your privacy. This extension does not collect, store, transmit, or sell any personal data.

⸻

2. Information We Collect

We do not collect any personal information.

Specifically:
	•	We do not collect names, email addresses, or contact details
	•	We do not collect browsing history
	•	We do not track user activity
	•	We do not collect analytics or usage data
	•	We do not use cookies
	•	We do not use tracking technologies

The extension only processes webpage content locally within your browser to detect media files when you activate it.

⸻

3. How the Extension Works

When you click the extension:
	•	It temporarily accesses the currently active tab
	•	It scans the page for media elements (images, videos, audio, SVG files)
	•	It displays detected media for you to download
	•	Downloads are initiated only when you choose to download a file

All processing occurs locally in your browser. No data is sent to external servers.

⸻

4. Permissions Explanation

The extension may request the following permissions:
	•	activeTab – To access the currently active page when you click the extension
	•	scripting – To scan the page for media elements
	•	downloads – To save selected media files to your device

These permissions are used strictly for the extension’s core functionality and for no other purpose.

⸻

5. Remote Code

This extension does not use remote code.
All functionality is contained within the packaged extension files.

⸻

6. Data Sharing

We do not:
	•	Sell data
	•	Share data
	•	Transfer data
	•	Store data externally

Because no personal data is collected, no data is shared with third parties.

⸻

7. Data Security

Since the extension does not collect or store user data, there is no personal data retained or stored on external servers.

